						               													<description>Zoo Square is a corner matching game that is visual challenging and addictively fun. It is designed for kids and adults who love zoo animals and into all kinds of crazy puzzles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal of the game is to be the fastest player to finish a 4-card puzzle. Four cards are randomly drawn from the deck, and you will need to arrange and rotate the 4 square cards into a 2x2 grid, so that the dangerous animals (elephants, lions, and crocodiles) are grouped by their kind, and fenced off from the free-roaming peacocks and the rest of the zoo.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A solution to the puzzle must meet the following two criteria:&amp;#10;1) The center 4 spaces contain the same kind of animals.&amp;#10;2) Each of the edge groups (made out of 2 spaces each) contain the same kind of animals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 2 game modes for beginner and advance level players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
